						               													<description>A cross between Scrabble and Yahtzee.  The game has 7 dice (16 in some other versions) with letters (and blank or square symbol for wild char). Carefully place your lettered dices to make high-scoring words in 1 minute turn. The game includes a dice shaker, a 1 min sand-timer and also a score pad (depending on the game version).  &amp;#10;Each player has 12 turns to score words into either the crossword section or the dice section on their scorepads. The crossword section works similarly to a traditional Scrabble board, so words must interlock and can score double and triple word and letter scores.  The dice section features entries for 2 to 7 letter words with fixed scores for each.  Bonus points can be achieved by getting a high total in the crossword section.&amp;#10;Some game versions with 16 dices, scorepad is not provided and there is no limits in lenght for word arrangement.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A 1-minute sand-timer is provided to limit each player's turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scrabble Dice is a word dice game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
